     "{\"template\":\"intro\",\"texts\":[\"Life's Journey is a road safety resource aimed at students aged 11-14.\"],\"link\":{\"image\":{}},\"image\":{},\"wrapped\":false}",
     "This resource tackles road safety and citizenship issues and looks at the positive and negative impacts of different forms of media.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h3\",\"value\":\"Materials\"}",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h4\",\"value\":\"Filmed scenarios\"}",
     "There are three filmed scenarios.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h4\",\"value\":\"Workshop films\"}",
     "Students can explore the messages in each scenario and are then encouraged to produce a performance and conduct their own surveys.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h4\",\"value\":\"Media tools\"}",
     "You can download films and audio, scripts, information sheets and posters.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h4\",\"value\":\"Interactive games\"}",
     "Students can participate in an engaging pairs game with 4 sub-games.",
     "{\"template\":\"htag\",\"level\":\"h4\",\"value\":\"Teachers' notes\"}",
     "This is a guide to using the resource, plus extension activities linked into curriculum subjects of English, Drama, PSHE and Citizenship.",
     "If you are a teacher and would like to request this resource for a London school, please email \u003ca href=\"mailto:educationandtraining@tfl.gov.uk?Subject=Life's%20Journey\"\u003eeducationandtraining@tfl.gov.uk\u003c/a\u003e with your name, email and phone number; school name and address and school contact."
    ],
